# launcher_smoke.numos — Phase 4A scripted-replay smoke.
#
# Goal: boot the emulator, let the splash animation finish, and screenshot the
# MainMenu launcher. Proves the script reader runs and can capture a frame.
#
# Timing note: with --deterministic --step-ms 16 the ~2 s splash finishes by
# ~frame 125. We wait 200 frames for a safe margin before capturing, so the
# screenshot is taken with the launcher fully settled. This wait is deliberate
# and explained — it is NOT tuned to a fragile exact frame.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/launcher_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/launcher.ppm --quiet

log "launcher_smoke: waiting for splash -> launcher"
wait 200

# Capture the launcher. The trailing --screenshot on the CLI also captures the
# final frame; this in-script shot proves the `screenshot` command itself works.
screenshot out/launcher.ppm
log "launcher_smoke: screenshot captured"
